# Typography

Typography is measured by the bounding box, which is based off the type size and line height.
These measurements in turn align with the spatial scale. Our type ramps are targeted to be screen size appropriate.
Although they each pull from our one Intuit type scale, the type sizes are adjusted based on desktop or mobile screens.

## Installation & Import

```bash
yarn add @ids-ts/typography
```

```tsx
import { Typography } from '@ids-ts/typography';
```

## Props

Typography exports semantic components: `D1`, `D2` (Display), `H1`–`H6` (Heading), `B1`–`B3` (Body). All share the same props.

| Prop | Type | Required | Description |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| `children` | `ReactNode` | Yes | Text content. |
| `as` | `string` | No | Override the rendered HTML element (e.g., `as="h3"` on `B2`). |
| `weight` | `'regular' \| 'demi' \| 'bold'` | No | Font weight override. |
| `style` | `CSSProperties` | No | Inline style overrides. |
| `className` | `string` | No | Additional CSS class names. |

## Token Usage

### Color

**container** — Container background, border, and surface colors
- `--color-container-background-accent`
- `--color-container-background-accent-active`
- `--color-container-background-accent-focus`

**text** — Primary and secondary text colors
- `--color-text-accent`
- `--color-text-complementary`
- `--color-text-disabled`

### Space

**container** — Container padding and internal spacing
- `--space-container-padding-large`
- `--space-container-padding-medium`
- `--space-container-padding-small`

### Radius

**radius** — Border radius for container corners
- `--radius-0`
- `--radius-10`
- `--radius-20`

### Font

**font** — Font family, size, weight, and line height
- `--font-size-12`
- `--font-size-14`
- `--font-size-16`

## Usage Patterns

### Alignment

```tsx
() => (
  <div style={{ display: 'flex', flexDirection: 'column', gap: '20px' }}>
    <div>
      <B2>Default text alignment</B2>
    </div>
    {/* Using inline styles */}
    <div style={{ textAlign: 'center' }}>
      <B2>Centered using inline styles</B2>
    </div>
  </div>
)
```

### H T M L Element

```tsx
() => (
  <div style={{ display: 'flex', flexDirection: 'column', gap: '20px' }}>
    <D1>A display renders as a div.</D1>
    <H2>A headline matches the heading number, so an H2 renders an h2.</H2>
    <B1>Body typography renders as a span.</B1>
  </div>
)
```

### Pairing

```tsx
() => (
  <>
    {/* Stack component used to space heading and body text */}
    <div
      style={{
        display: 'flex',
        flexDirection: 'column',
        gap: `${tokens.intuit.light.size.size1}`
      }}
    >
      <B2 as="h3" weight="demi">
        B2 styling, used as an `h3` element
      </B2>
      {/* Stack component used to space paragraphs */}
      <div
        style={{
          display: 'flex',
          flexDirection: 'column',
          gap: `${tokens.intuit.light.size.size3}`
        }}
      >
        <B3>
          By using a stack component, any subsequent paragraph will be
          automatically spaced.
        </B3>
        <B3>
          Nulla efficitur tellus convallis leo semper pretium. Maecenas
          venenatis sem urna, non dapibus magna condimentum vel. Pellentesque et
          nunc sit amet quam blandit volutpat ultrices congue est. Pellentesque
          habitant morbi tristique senectus et netus et malesuada fames ac
          turpis egestas.
        </B3>
      </div>
    </div>
  </>
)
```

### Weight

```tsx
() => (
  <div
    style={{
      display: 'flex',
      flexDirection: 'column',
      gap: '40px'
    }}
  >
    <H3>
      Text that has <strong>partial bolding</strong> automatically applied using
      `strong` tags.
    </H3>
    {/* Avoid <H3 as={Bold}>Hello world!</B2>, instead: */}
    <H3 weight="bold">
      This text has the same font weight override applied throughout and still
      renders the semantic HTML tag.
    </H3>
    <div
      style={{
        backgroundColor: `${tokens.intuit.dark.color.colorContainerBackgroundPrimary}`,
        padding: `${tokens.intuit.light.size.size8}`,
        color: `${tokens.intuit.dark.color.colorTextPrimary}`
      }}
    >
      <B1 weight="demi">
        Demi weight rendered as light text against a dark background
      </B1>
      <B1
        weight="demi"
        style={{
          WebkitFontSmoothing: 'antialiased',
          MozOsxFontSmoothing: 'grayscale'
        }}
      >
        Demi weight using additional CSS to compensate for MacOS + Chrome
      </B1>
    </div>
  </div>
)
```

